{
  "texts": [
    "Increasing N w implies less perceptibility of REGTEXT.",
    "Lastly, as we raise the threshold for perturbation using w min, where w min ={1, 5, 10, 12} corresponds 100%, 95%, 85% and 80% of the total examples perturbed.",
    "REGTEXT's performance remains consistently below zero-shot levels as shown in Fig. 4b, with the most drop observed when 100% of the data is perturbed with REGTEXT.",
    "b) Impact of LoRA adapter rank.",
    "Q-LoRA (Dettmers et al., 2024) is commonly used to finetune pre-trained LMs, with the adapter rank controlling the number of trainable parameters."
  ]
}